Description:
The overflow property controls what happens when content inside a box overflows its set size. Common values:

visible (default, content spills out)

hidden (content is clipped)

scroll (scrollbars appear)

auto (scrollbars appear only if needed)


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Overflow Property</title>
  <style>
    .overflow-box {
      width: 300px;
      height: 100px;
      border: 2px solid #f94144;
      padding: 10px;
      overflow: auto;
      background-color: #f9c74f;
    }

    .content {
      width: 500px;
      height: 150px;
      background-color: #f3722c;
      color: white;
      padding: 10px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h2>15. Overflow Property</h2>

  <div class="overflow-box">
    <div class="content">
      This content is bigger than the container, so scrollbars appear because overflow is set to auto.
    </div>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
